{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774535003,"nonce":"6V+q2FamnvmNXunFlu7261qRNC8=","title":"Vmap adversarial training replicates","message":"Train all replicates in single vmapped process instead of separate OS processes.\n\nPreviously the adversarial phase extracted only replicate 0 from the warmup ensemble,\nrequiring 5 separate OS processes (with different seeds) to get 5 replicates. This was\nwasteful (5x redundant warmup, 5x host memory, caused OOM on the pod).\n\nThe fix vmaps the entire adversarial training loop over the replicate axis, so a single\nprocess trains all N replicates simultaneously — matching how TaskTrainer handles warmup.","files":null}]}